# reddit.cli

reddit.cli is a command-line tool that fetches a random post from the front page of Reddit and either prints the post details or opens the post in a web browser.

## Installation

To use reddit.cli, you need to have Node.js installed on your system. You can download it from [https://nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org).

Once you have Node.js installed, you can install reddit.cli globally using npm:

npm install -g reddit.cli

## Usage

After installing reddit.cli, you can use it from the command line by typing `reddit` followed by optional flags.

reddit [--print]

This will fetch a random post from the front page of Reddit. If you use the `--print` flag, it will print the post details to the console. Without the `--print` flag, it will open the post in a web browser.

### Flags

- `--print`: Prints the details of the random post to the console. If this flag is not provided, the post will be opened in a web browser.

## Dependencies

reddit.cli has the following dependencies:

- node-fetch: ^3.3.1
- open: ^9.1.0
- yargs: ^17.7.2

These dependencies will be automatically installed when you run `npm install` to install reddit.cli.

